commText: Philip Salt and Narine are at the crease. Philip Salt is on strike. Siraj will open the attack
Siraj to Philip Salt, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, Salt went hard on the cut and dragged an inside edge to the on-side

Siraj to Philip Salt, SIX, a leading edge and the ball sails over the ropes for a maximum - third man was inside the ring and this was a safe shot, back of a length and holding its line on middle, Salt was early into the pull, gets a fat leading edge and the ball lobs over the infield

Siraj to Philip Salt, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Salt - back of a length and at the stumps, he picks the length early, swivels across and then thumps the pull over mid-wicket, one bounce and over the ropes
Siraj to Philip Salt, leg byes, 1 run, much better from Siraj, pitched up around middle, Salt was pushing away from his body and missed, off the pad and rolled to the off-side for a leg-bye
Siraj to Narine, no run, fuller length delivery and just outside off - Narine backs away, clears his left and then watches it go through to the keeper
Siraj to Narine, leg byes, 1 run, full and at the pads, Narine's cramped for room on the flick and missed, off the pad and rolled to the off-side for a leg-bye
Yash Dayal, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Yash Dayal to Narine, no run, that's a perfect leg-stump yorker and Narine has been smashed on his toes, he's limping across and looks in visible discomfort - very full and following Narine as he backed away, crashed into his boot even before he could get his bat down, the ball rolled to the off-side even as Narine limped across in agony
RCB in day vs night games since IPL 2023 Day games: Four wins in four games Night games: Four wins in 17 games Each of their four wins in day games came when they batted first.
Salt vs Siraj in IPL 3 inngs 17 balls 47 runs 3 X 4s | 5 X 6s No dismissals SR 276.47
The physio has come out to have a look at Narine, he's stretching his right leg, shouldn't be too serious though and he's back on his feet
Yash Dayal to Narine, no run, low full-toss from Dayal, was looking for the yorker, Narine jams an inside edge on the drive and mistimes it to mid-on
Yash Dayal to Narine, leg byes, 1 run, another leg-stump yorker from Dayal, he's bowling to a plan and is giving nothing in Narine's zone - rolls off the pads to square leg for a leg-bye
Yash Dayal to Philip Salt, FOUR, creamed, the inswinger from Dayal, but it's a tad too full, allows Salt to back away and drill the drive over wide cover, runs away to the ropes in a hurry

Yash Dayal to Philip Salt, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Salt, they've kept Narine quiest, but Salt's off to a flier - backs away, opens up the off-side and then drives it straight of mid-off for a boundary
Yash Dayal to Philip Salt, 2 runs, fuller length delivery on the pads, clipped in front of square on the on-side - long chase in the deep and they're back for the second
Siraj to Narine, no run, Siraj keeps it full and wide of off, an aimless swing and Narine is beaten by miles
Kohli has a chat with the bowler
Siraj to Narine, no run, Siraj keeps it full and gets it to angle across the left-hander, Narine styas leg-sided, throws his hands on the drive and misses by a long way
Siraj to Narine, FOUR, just over cover, but Narine is off and away, low full-toss outside off, Narine swipes and connects, gets enough on the shot to clear the man in the ring
Siraj to Narine, no run, the slower short ball from Siraj, banged in short and pushed across the left-hander, Narine swings and misses, on the bounce to Karthik
Siraj to Narine, no run, this is good bowling from Siraj, on a good length and pushed across the left-hander, left alone
Siraj to Narine, no run, banged in short and angling across the left-hander, Narine lets it go on height, but it ain't wided, just one boundary and five dots off the over
Lockie Ferguson, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Ferguson to Philip Salt, SIX, crunched, tad too short from Ferguson - Salt swivels across, picks the length and then deposits it over deep square leg for a maximum

Ferguson to Philip Salt, FOUR, streaky and four, on a good length and holding its line on off, Salt swings hard, gets a thin inside edge and the ball; races away fine, past the leg-stump and into the ropes
Ferguson to Philip Salt, FOUR, slapped, on a length and well wide of off, Salt gets on top of the bounce and then clatters it over cover-point, he's off to a proper flier

Ferguson to Philip Salt, SIX, this is an expensive start from Ferguson - length ball on off, Salt gets forward and then thumps it over mid-off, went sailing all the way. They have kept Narine quiet, but Salt has made up for it already
Ferguson to Philip Salt, FOUR, this is exceptional hitting from Salt - slower ball from Ferguson, but it's a full-toss and it's drilled through extra-cover for another boundary
Ferguson to Philip Salt, FOUR, 28 off the over, another slower ball from Ferguson, but it's right in the slot for Salt to drill it back over his head, one bounce and over the ropes
Once again RCB under the pump, they had a plan for Narine, but they forgot one for Salt and are paying the penalty. A 3rd over for Siraj
Siraj to Narine, 1 run,short of a good length and at the body, pulled past square leg for a single
Siraj to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Siraj to Philip Salt, out Caught by Rajat Patidar!! Respite for RCB, they've got rid of Philip Salt at last. On a good length and angling into the right-hander, Salt picked the length early and then swung through the line, he was looking to go behind square, but hit it a lot straighter and over square leg - Patidar runs across to his right and completes a simple catch. They looked lost in that lost over, but this is a small opening for the men in green. Philip Salt c Rajat Patidar b Siraj 48(14) [4s-7 6s-3]
Angkrish Raghuvanshi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Siraj to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, leg byes, 1 run, short of a good length and at the pads, Raghuvanshi was looking to flick and gets an inside edge onto the pad, rolled towards square leg for a single

Siraj to Narine, FOUR, ugly and four, nothing you can do as a bowler in this format? A slower ball, tad too full though, Narine throws his arms on the drive and squirts it off the thick inner half, places it wide of Kohli at mid-on and beats him to the ropes
STAT: Only the fourth wicket for an RCB seamer in 40.2 overs in Powerplay this season
Siraj to Narine, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven with an open face past cover for a single

Siraj to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, leg byes, 1 run, shourt for LBW, but this is clearly sliding down leg and RCB don't review, full-toss on the pads and Raghuvanshi was beaten on the flick, rolled backward of square on the on-side for a leg-bye
Summary (Overs 1-5) > Salt gets off to a brisk start > RCB manage to keep Narine quiet > Salt bashes Ferguson for 28 in his first over > Siraj ends Salt’s blitz
Yash Dayal [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
50+ opening partnerships for KKR since 2022 \nSalt - Narine: Three in seven innings \nOther pairs: Three in 28 innings

Yash Dayal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, 3 runs, a gentle chip and Raghuvanshi has enough to clear Faf at mid-off - on a good length and just outside off , Raghuvanshi was shaping for the drive, but it came off the bottom half and popped up in the air. Good chase from faf to prevent the boundary
Yash Dayal to Narine, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Dayal to Narine, out Caught by Kohli!! A rare failure for Narine against RCB - they kept him quiet with a string of yorkers, both at the pads and outside off - now Dayal delivers the sucker punch, throws a slower ball wide of off and Narine can't resist the lofted drive, but he gets it right off the toe of the bat, there's a fielder at long-off for that shot and Kohli doesn't drop those. Narine c Kohli b Yash Dayal 10(15) [4s-2]
Venkatesh Iyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Dayal to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, lovely, intent from Venkatesh - comes down the pitch, takes the momentum into the drive and clears mid-off, bounces away to the ropes

Yash Dayal to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Venkatesh - pitched up by Dayal, he leans forward, presents a straight bat and then caresses the drive wide of mid-off, no chance for Kohli
Yash Dayal to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, Dayal drags the length back outside off, dabbed behind square on the off-side for a single
Yash Dayal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Dayal to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, out Caught by Green!! That's a stunner and it could only be Green with that super hero effort. On a length and angling into the right-hander, Raghuvanshi leaned across and then chipped it nonchalantly over mid-wicket - any other fielder and there was a boundary for the taking, but Green back-tracks, keeps his eyes on the ball, it was dropping over his right shoulder, but he arches back and takes a one-handed corker, even as he fell on his back. Faf enjoyed that, Green is chuffed to bits, two wickets in the over and RCB finish the batting PP on a high. They've taken the strategic break as well. Angkrish Raghuvanshi c Green b Yash Dayal 3(4)
Highest Powerplay totals for three wickets or more down (IPL) 75/3 KKR vs RCB Kolkata 2024 * 72/3 MI vs GT Ahmedabad 2023 71/3 MI vs RR Wankhede 2014 65/3 RR vs GT Navi Mumbai 2023
Shreyas Iyer, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Lockie Ferguson [1.0-0-28-0] is back into the attack
Ferguson to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, punched into the gap wide of cover for a single
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, short of a length and into the body, tucked to the right of mid-wicket for a single
Ferguson to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, banged in short as Venkatesh came down the pitch, looked awkward as he fended it uppishly through mid-wicket
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, beautifully played, half-volley from Ferguson - Shreyas leans across, presents the full face of the bat and then drives it straight of mid-on for a boundary
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, no run, Ferguson shortens the length on off, Shreyas prods across and pushes it back at the bowler
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, short of a length and well wide of off, slapped to deep point for a single

Fourth time in eight games this season RCB have conceded 70+ runs inside the Powerplay - the most by any team in a single edition of IPL CSK 62/1 PBKS 40/1 KKR 85/0 LSG 54/1 RR 54/1 MI 72/0 SRH 76/0 KKR 75/3
Time for spin and it's Karn Sharma
Karn Sharma, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, a friendly full-toss and it's whipped through mid-wicket for a single
Karn Sharma to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, tossed up on off, Venkatesh plants hi8s front-foot across and drives it to long-on
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, poor ball from Karn - drifts one full and down leg, Shreyas gets across, plays with an angled bat and runs it fine, beats the diving fielder in the deep
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, no run, tossed up on middle, Shreyas leans across and turns it to the on-side
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, that's so easy for Shreyas - dragged short by Karn, he rocks back and then pulls it over square leg, bisects the two fielders in the deep with ease
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, no run, lovely, much better from Karn - the leg-break, drifts in with the angle, draws Shreyas forward and then spins past the outside edge
Another bowling change and it's Green
Cameron Green, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Green to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, lovely, they're finding the boundaries with ease, on a length and angling into the left-hander - Venkatesh brings the length into play, a straight-batted on-drive and he beats Kohli to his left at mid-on
Green to Venkatesh Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Green to Venkatesh Iyer, out Caught by Lomror!! .. and Venkatesh has thrown his wicket away - banged in short and at the left-hander, Venkatesh swivelled across on the pull, the idea was right, but got it high off the bat, lots of height and no real distance. Lomror runs across and then completes a simple catch. RCB have conceded plenty of boundaries, but they've also chipped away at the wickets. Venkatesh Iyer c Lomror b Green 16(8) [4s-3]
Rinku Singh, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Green to Rinku Singh, no run, banged in short and angling across the left-hander, left alone
Green to Rinku Singh, no run, tad fuller and at the stumps, pushed back at the bowler
Green to Rinku Singh, FOUR, another batter gets going with a boundary - short and at the body, Rinku swivelled across, rolled his wrists and then muscled the pull past square leg for a boundary
Green to Rinku Singh, 1 run, short and at the body, pulled down to long leg for a single
Karn Sharma to Rinku Singh, 1 run, tossed up on off, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, flatter and at the stumps, worked through mid-wicket for a single
Karn Sharma to Rinku Singh, 1 run, Karn drifts one on middle, Rinku Singh lunges across and nudges it to short fine, he's called for a quick single by Shreyas who beats the throw at his end
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, no run, tossed up on middle, Shreyas prods well forward on the defensive push
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, no run, slower and wider of off, Shreyas drives and can't beat Ferguson at backward point

Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, 2 runs, excellent fielding from Siraj, saved two runs for his team - was nicely tossed up as Shreyas reversed the stance on the sweep, was bouncing away to the square boundary, but Siraj gets across and manages to push it back into play
Summary (Overs 6-10) > Dayal strikes twice in an over > Green takes a spectacular catch > Venky Iyer holes out in the deep > RCB fight to keep the scoring rate down
Green to Rinku Singh, wide, dug in short and way too short, Rinku Singh bends and lets it go, rightly called a wide
Green to Rinku Singh, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on a good length on the middle and leg line, tucked to deep square leg
Green to Shreyas Iyer, no run, dug in short outside off, Shreyas Iyer plays a half-hearted pull and the ball is close to the top-edge, nothing on UltraEdge and RCB did well not to review that
Green to Shreyas Iyer, no run, slower delivery full outside off, driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
Green to Shreyas Iyer, no run, short of length and angling into off-stump, pushed to cover
Green to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, nicely done, Shreyas Iyer shuffles across and takes the fullish delivery from outside off, lofts and beats Kohli to his right at long-on
Green to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, direct-hit and Shreyas Iyer might well have been short. Full outside off, driven to mid-off and he takes on Faf, just misses the direct-hit
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, pushed through on the pads, Shreyas Iyer gives the charge but adjusts and turns to mid-wicket
Karn Sharma to Rinku Singh, 1 run, tossed up full on the stumps, Rinku Singh clears his front leg and drives to long-on
Karthik looks to be hyper-active today. Screaming and screeching around.

Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, leg byes, 1 run, tossed up outside off, Shreyas Iyer turns around for the reverse-sweep, misses, off the pad to Yash Dayal at short third man who gets an earful from DK for not stopping that
Karn Sharma to Rinku Singh, 2 runs, fraction short and turning back in on middle, Rinku Singh goes on the back foot to pull to deep mid-wicket for a couple
Karn Sharma to Rinku Singh, SIX, that's a fine shot. It's tossed up outside off, Rinku Singh comes down the track and lofts straight down the ground, held the shape and it flies away for a biggie
Karn Sharma to Rinku Singh, 1 run, this is a wild slog, again gives the charge and looks to loft, heaves it off a thick inside-edge to deep backward square leg
Green to Rinku Singh, no run, Rinku Singh comes down the track to attack Green, dug in short and he pulls and misses
Green to Rinku Singh, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on a good length on the stumps, nudged to deep backward square leg

Green to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, tough caught and bowled chance goes down. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, driven to the left of Green who sticks his hand out and it does not go in, slaps the turf in disappointment
Green to Rinku Singh, FOUR, mid-on is on and Rinku Singh takes a calculated risk, comes down the track and lofts, does not get all of it but clears Faf and it's one bounce over the ropes
Green to Rinku Singh, 1 run, tight good length delivery on off, dabbed with an open face to third man
Green to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, nicely done. Dug in short at Shreyas Iyer, short third man was in, Iyer arches his back, ramps it over Karthik
Lockie Ferguson [2.0-0-36-0] is back into the attack
Ferguson to Rinku Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Ferguson to Rinku Singh, out Caught by Yash Dayal!! Ferguson is pumped. A vital wicket. A slower ball leg-cutter outside the leg-stump, Rinku Singh sinks low to heave and it's off the glove, straight to the fielder at short fine-leg. Dolly catch and the dangerous Rinku goes. Rinku Singh c Yash Dayal b Ferguson 24(16) [4s-2 6s-1]
Andre Russell, right handed bat, comes to the crease

DreRuss is out caught behind but he has reviewed it. He is reviewing for it to be over the waist. Was a high full-toss. Big moment in the game here. Everyone wait anxiously. Meanwhile shouts of "RCB" do the rounds.

Ferguson to Russell, no ball, clearly over the waist and it will be a free-hit for Russell next. A high full-toss at Russell who was surprised, was backing away, edged it low to DK who took it. The square leg umpire does not signal a no-ball so Russell surprised reviews and replays show that it was well over the waist
Ferguson to Russell, 1 run, the free-hit ball is a back of a length delivery tucking up Russell who pulls wide of short square leg, just one
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, slower ball leg-cutter full on the pads, Shreyas Iyer closes the face of the bat too early and the leading-edge just clears the leaping Ferguson
Ferguson to Russell, 1 run, another slower ball on a good length and on leg-stump, Russell turns it wide of short square leg
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, no run, back of a length outside off, dabbed to short third man and Russell does not want the single
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, back of a length and following Shreyas Iyer who makes room and cuts to sweeper cover
Karn Sharma [3.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, that is sloppy from Faf at cover, Shreyas Iyer shimmies all around, then pushes it to Faf who lets it go
Slip in for Russell.
Karn Sharma to Russell, no run, slower and good length on the stumps, Russell adjusts to defend off the back foot

Karn Sharma to Russell, 1 run, down leg, Russell misses the sweep, but it flicks the back of the bat as he completes his swing, Green anticipates from sleep and takes pace off the shot with a diving half-stop
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, no run, slower and tossed up just outside the leg-stump, Shreyas Iyer gets forward to flick across the line, misses, the ball rolls near DK
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, good shot, it's tossed up outside off, turning away, Shreyas Iyer brings out the reverse-sweep and gets it over backward point for four
Karn Sharma to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, pushed through on leg-stump, Shreyas Iyer gets forward to knock it to long-on
Summary (Overs 11-15) > KKR continue to score steadily > Green puts down a return chance > Ferguson gets rid of Rinku > Russell is caught off a waist-high no-ball
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, short of length on off, defended wide of short third man for an easy single
Ferguson to Russell, 1 run, pacy short ball at Russell who takes it on, miscued and it falls in front of fine-leg coming in, got lucky there, did Russell
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on a good length outside off, driven hard and straight to sweeper cover
Ferguson to Russell, 1 run, short on the stumps, Russell makes room and dabs to third man
Ferguson to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, short and wide outside off, cut on the bounce to deep backward point
Ferguson to Russell, 1 run, slower ball full leg-cutter outside off, driven wide of Faf at mid-off who gets across and cuts it off
Timeout! RCB doing well not to allow Russell to get away. But still 190-200 is on from here.
Yash Dayal [2.0-0-22-2] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Russell, FOUR, bad ball and four. A low full-toss outside off, driven hard and wide of sweeper cover who can't get across in time
Yash Dayal to Russell, no run, full and wide outside off, just inside the tramline, Russell nearly falls over as he drives and misses
Yash Dayal to Russell, no ball&byes, FOUR, what a bad ball. It's a front foot no-ball and it's well down leg too, no chance for DK, even with a full-length dive. 5 and a free-hit next
Yash Dayal to Russell, wide, way way outside off, does not even land on the cutstrip, way past it in fact, and the free-hit stays
Yash Dayal to Russell, 1 run, caught at extra-cover but it does not matter as it's a free-hit. Dug in short outside off, Russell mistimes the cut and it lobs to the fielder
Yash Dayal to Shreyas Iyer, wide, full and wide outside off, just wide of the tramline, left alone and wide

Yash Dayal to Shreyas Iyer, no run, the towel on Yash Dayal's back falls off as he runs in, full outside off, driven to extra-cover and Jacks saves four with a diving stop. Iyer mentions the towel to the ump, was he distracted by that moment?
Yash Dayal to Shreyas Iyer, SIX, back of the hand slower ball on a good length outside off, Shreyas Iyer gets forward and hammers the loft and it's all the way over long-off, mid-off was in

Yash Dayal to Shreyas Iyer, FOUR, wide of the crease and a half-volley outside off, crunched straight down the ground and beats the desperate diving effort of Faf at long-off, the ball dribbles to touch the cushion. 50 for Shreyas Iyer
Cameron Green [3.0-0-27-1] is back into the attack
Green to Russell, wide, dug in short and down leg, Russell ducks to leave, called a wide and RCB review. Clearly above the head and it's a wide
Green to Russell, leg byes, 1 run, full and into the pads, outside the leg-stump, Russell flicks and misses, takes a legbye
Green to Shreyas Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Green to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by du Plessis!! Fine catch at long-off. Full outside off, Shreyas Iyer slices the loft but Faf gets across and dives to take it to his right. Judged it well and Shreyas can't believe it. Shreyas Iyer c du Plessis b Green 50(36) [4s-7 6s-1]
Ramandeep Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Green to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, full on middle, Ramandeep Singh shuffles across and exposes all his stumps, flicks to mid-wicket
Green to Russell, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Russell drags the pull to deep mid-wicket. A grunt of frustration from Russell for not timing it
Green to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, good yorker on off, dug out to mid-wicket
Green to Russell, FOUR, finally Russell puts one away. A back of a length delivery on middle, swung away wide of deep mid-wicket
Mohammed Siraj [3.0-0-20-1] is back into the attack
Siraj to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, fullish outside off, Ramandeep Singh stands deep and lofts over deep mid-wicket, such a clean hit and sails into the crowd. Was the cross-seamer
Siraj to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, again a slot ball - full and in the slot outside off, half-volley and Ramandeep lofts over Kohli at long-off who just watched it fly

Siraj to Ramandeep Singh, FOUR, this is a good ball, yorker length outside off, Ramandeep Singh digs it out and just gets it past the dive of short third man to his left, the fielder went with an outstretched left hand but it just missed him
Siraj to Ramandeep Singh, wide, full and just outside the leg-stump, Ramandeep Singh shuffles across gets inside the line, heaves and misses, called a wide
Siraj to Ramandeep Singh, no run, slower ball dug in outside off, Ramandeep Singh pulls and misses. A precious dot
Siraj to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, full outside off, Ramandeep Singh lofts and it's off the thick inside half, wide of mid-on for one, Russell is happy with just one
Siraj to Russell, wide, horrid delivery down leg, short and well down leg, DK did well to move to collect
Siraj to Russell, 1 run, full and wide outside off, dug out to deep backward point and Russell retains the strike with that run
Only once has RCB successfully chased down a 200+ target in IPL: 204 vs PBKS in Bengaluru in 2010
Yash Dayal [3.0-0-40-2] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Russell, FOUR, a low full-toss outside off, Russell reaches for it and slices it to the deep backward point fence, one bounce over the ropes. Russell starts the over well

Yash Dayal to Russell, FOUR, right off the toe of the bat but four more, a slower ball on a good length outside off, Russell pulls and it's to the deep mid-wicket fence, wide of both long-on and deep mid-wicket
Yash Dayal to Russell, 1 run, fine yorker on the stumps, Russell digs it out to short fine-leg, just one
Yash Dayal to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, back of the hand slower ball outside off, dug in short, Ramandeep Singh pulls to deep mid-wicket and gives the strike back to Russell
Faf has a word with Yash Dayal.
Not called a wide. Russell reviews. Over the head - so a wide.
Yash Dayal to Russell, wide, good review by Russell. Just over the head as it is dug in short outside off, Russell looks to slash and misses
Yash Dayal to Russell, 1 run, fine yorker on the stumps, tailing in, Russell digs it out
Yash Dayal to Ramandeep Singh, FOUR, KKR end with 222. A short ball outside off, Ramandeep Singh ramps it one bounce over the ropes at third man, short third man was in

17:26 Local Time, 11:56 GMT, 17:26 IST: KKR will be happy with this total. Salt at the top was like a runaway train and he set the tone. Narine was kept quiet though by very good bowling into the pads and outside his reach. He did not make many and RCB fought back with wickets after Salt went. But Shreyas Iyer held one end up and made his first fifty of the season. Contributions from Rinku and Russell helped KKR as they looked for a 200-plus score. At the end Ramandeep Singh played a blinder and his innings just gave KKR the extra 10-15 runs. For most parts RCB executed very well especially to Narine and Russell. The plans were good from RCB who stuck to it for the majority of the innings and Green was the pick of the bowlers. Will be a stiff chase for RCB. Can they do it? Back for the reply shortly...
Welcome back. Harshit Rana has the new-ball. A wide slip in.

Ramandeep Singh - I just wanted to whack the ball, luckily it was my day. Slow bumpers were not easy to hit, that's what we will do. 222 is a really good score on this pitch, pace on the ball is easy to hit. All credit to Abhishek Nayar, he prepares us this way and all our net sessions resembles a match. We've got a legend in the side in Narine and we will want to watch the legend on show today.
RCB bowling in last three matches vs MI: 199/3 in 15.3 overs (RR 12.83) vs SRH: 287/3 in 20 overs (RR 14.35) vs KKR: 222/6 in 20 overs (RR 11.10)
222/6 is Knight Riders' joint highest total against Royal Challengers equalling 222/3 in the inaugural IPL match in 2008
Most 220+ totals in an IPL season 3 by CSK in 2023 3 by SRH in 2024 3 by KKR in 2024
KKR innings progression Powerplay: 75/3 (RR 12.50) Middle overs: 74/2 (RR 8.22) Death overs: 73/1 (RR 14.60)
